{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe auto-lander is a long-running service; it must deploy like the review-bot and log to its OWN service logs — writing to `session_log` would blur that type's purpose (it is for agentic sessions, not CI/infra processes).\n\n## What\nContainerize the service and wire it into docker-compose (single instance) on the existing Gerrit box; route logs to container stdout → the existing CloudWatch monitoring.\n\n## Dependencies\nDepends on **S2** (the core loop): this story packages and deploys the loop service, so there must be a service to containerize; the deploy is otherwise independent of the failure/command stories.\n\n## Scope\nDeploy + observability + single-instance guard. Not the loop logic.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` + a compose service in `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`.\n- [ ] **Single-instance guard:** the container acquires a file/advisory lock in its state volume on start (so two copies never drive concurrently), backed by `deploy.replicas: 1` in compose.\n- [ ] **Credentials (AC2 mechanism):** `autolander-bot`/RebarBotNava's `rebaseOnBehalfOfUploader` is a **server-level capability** granted in `All-Projects` `refs/meta/config` (`[capability]` / service-user grant), not a per-project label ACL; plus submit permission on `refs/heads/*`. The Gerrit HTTP token is provisioned as an SSM **SecureString** (`infra/terraform/ssm.tf`, fetched by `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh`) — never inlined.\n- [ ] **Observability (AC3):** logs go to container stdout; `infra/scripts/observability.sh` greps the container (`CONTAINER_NAME=compose-autolander-1`) for an `AUTOLANDER_ERROR` marker and emits `PutMetricData` to `rebar/host:autolander_errors`, with an alarm in `infra/terraform/monitoring_*.tf`. The service NEVER writes `session_log`.\n- [ ] **Liveness/restart (AC4):** a `HEALTHCHECK` in `Dockerfile.autolander` + `restart: unless-stopped` in compose; a hung/crashed container is caught by the health check + restart policy (surfaced via the `autolander_errors` metric). (The `wipChain`-timeout parking of a stuck stack is loop logic owned by S2/S3, not this deploy story.)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783725984581080001,"uuid":"81231946-0af0-414e-a436-5f94fd4e850f"}